                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1ra" to="303rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102691"> Thomas Aquinas </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Summa theologiae II-II</title>
                                <incipit>Post comunem consideracionem de virtutibus et viciis et aliis ad moralem materiam </incipit>
                                <explicit>nisi forte quando pugiles sunt valde inpares uirtute et arte et cetera</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> The text starts with ST II-II, prologue; ends with ST II-II q. 95, art. 10. <locus from="120ra" to="124ra" scheme="folios"/> are identical to <locus from="115va" to="119rb" scheme="folios"/>. This has been commented upon by a contemporary hand, which has marked the end of <locus from="119rb" to="119rb" scheme="folios"/> with <quote>sequitur quartus inmediate signo tali</quote> and a signe-de-renvoi, which is repated after line 11 on <locus from="124ra" to="124ra" scheme="folios"/>; in addition, <locus from="120r" to="123v" scheme="folios"/> are marked in the top and bottom margin with the words <quote>vacat</quote> and <quote>superfluit</quote>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="303v" to="303v" scheme="folios"/>: guidelines, but no text.</p>
                                </note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107449">Opera omnia</title>
                                    <citedRange from="8" to="9" unit="volume"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="304rb" to="310va" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">List of headings</title>
                                <note>List of headings covered by the previous text. On <locus from="310rb" to="310rb" scheme="folios"/> the final rubric reads: <quote>Tantum de registro illius prime partis secunda secunde sancti thome</quote>. However, on <locus from="310va" to="310va" scheme="folios"/> the list continues with the headings for ST q. 92-95.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="311ra" to="312rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Sermon</title>
                                <rubric>Assit in ?primo? sancta maria et cetera</rubric>
                                <incipit>Auctoritates sacre scripture lucas 17 Cum omnia feceritis (Luke 17:10)</incipit>
                                <explicit>Et in aue maria petimus quod domina nostra impetret nobis quod in pater noster orauimus Amen</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Deo gracias et cetera </finalRubric>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locusGrp>
                                    <locus from="312va" to="364vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <locus from="369ra" to="376va" scheme="folios"/>
                                </locusGrp>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102685"> Thomas Ebendorfer </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Tractatus de confessione</title>
                                <rubric>TRactatus de confessione</rubric>
                                <incipit>Ecce nunc tempus acceptabile (2 Corinth. 6:2) dicit Apostolus 2<hi rend="super">a</hi> ad corinthos 6<hi rend="super">o </hi>Haymo exponens uerba premissa dicit</incipit>
                                <explicit>Sapiens sibi uidetur diues pauper autem prudens scrutabitur eum et cetera Amen </explicit>
                                <finalRubric>Expliciunt collaciones Reuerendi magistri necnon Egregii doctoris Thome de haselbach de confessione Et hoc de u<hi rend="super">e</hi> sensibus Deo gracias et cetera</finalRubric>
                                <note>The final part of the text is in disorder due to faulty rebinding. The end of the text is found on <locus from="358va" to="358va" scheme="folios"/>. The correct order may be <locus from="369" to="376" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="360" to="364" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="359" to="359" scheme="folios"/>, and finally <locus from="358" to="358" scheme="folios"/>. However, this is not enitirely certain, sinc a comparison has only been made with other manuscripts containing the text, because of the lack of a modern edition.</note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locusGrp>
                                    <locus from="358va" to="358vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <locus from="365ra" to="368vb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <locus from="377ra" to="378va" scheme="folios"/>
                                </locusGrp>
                                <title type="desc">Indulgences and papal bulls</title>
                                <rubric>Indulgencie</rubric>
                                <incipit>Item dominus iohannes papa xxii diuinum cultum </incipit>
                                <explicit>Sanctus thomas in scripto ?super? distinctio 22 pena non potest tolli manente culpa et cetera</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p> Copies of different indulgences and bulls by the following popes:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="358va" to="358va" scheme="folios"/>: John XXII;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="365ra" to="365ra" scheme="folios"/>: Eugene IV;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="365vb" to="365vb" scheme="folios"/>: Clement VI;</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="367va" to="367va" scheme="folios"/>: Nicholas V.</p>
                                    <p> The seven leaves containing these texts are disordered due to faulty rebinding.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
