                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="13v" to="337r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Scattered additions in the margin by the scribe or a contemporary hand, and at least one additional hand. The marginal text consist of corrections, additions of omitted text keyed to the main text with signes-de-renvoi, and glossing; e.g. on <locus from="133v" to="133v" scheme="folios"/>, a refrence to another chapter or text. There are also some manicules and nota marks, e.g. on <locus from="80v" to="80v" scheme="folios"/>. On <locus from="290v" to="297r" scheme="folios"/> a modern hand has marked chapters in pencil.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="24rb" to="24rb" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>A red paragraph initial has been corrected from <quote>A</quote> to <quote>D</quote> in black ink.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="119r" to="124r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>A medieval hand has marked the beginning and end of a section of superfluous text.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="357v" to="370r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Modern annotations in pencil in outer corners: <quote>a-ö.</quote>
                                    </note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
