                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in black or brown ink, capitals touched in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1ra" to="1ra" scheme="folios"/>: opening historiated initial P over 18 lines in gold, outlined in red and black ink with flourishing in red. The counterspace contains an image of Thomas Aquinas seated at a lectern, which has an open book on it. At the master's feet are five seated monks, three of which have covered heads and are holding open books. On the master's shoulder sits a white dove and on his head a hat. The image is painted in thick opaque colours. The main colours are: yellow for the lectern, white and black for the clothes and a blue background. The initial extends into a 3/4 border of green acanthus leaves and with red and blue flowers. <locus from="1va" to="291rb" scheme="folios"/>: chapters are opened by plain initials over 2-6 lines in red. From <locus from="292ra" to="301vb" scheme="folios"/> there is spaced reserved for intitials, but no initials. <locus from="311ra" to="311ra" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="312va" to="312va" scheme="folios"/>: texts opened by a plain initial over 3 lines in red. <locus from="313ra" to="375va" scheme="folios"/>: paragraphs opened by plain initials over 2-4 lines in red.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
